---
title: Italian Meatball Soup with Orzo, Kale, and Carrot
description: This is soup the way your Italian grandma would’ve made it. Naturally, there’s a soul-soothing broth flavored with Tuscan herbs. And it’s got all the veggies—like kale, carrot, and onion—to make you strong. But that old-world charm really shines through in the pork meatballs, orzo pasta, and garlic toasts. If you want to claim this one as a generations-old family recipe, we’ll keep it a secret.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/5c477ed0c445fa5d6d508ef2-6b30237e.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/italian-meatball-soup-5c477ed0c445fa5d6d508ef2-47f8ded2.pdf
time required: 35m
servings: 2
nutrition:
  calories: 850 kcal
  fat: 47 g
  saturated fat: 19 g
  carbohydrates: 66 g
  sugar: 9 g
  protein: 41 g
  fiber: 7 g
  sodium: 1380 mg
author: HelloFresh
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/italian-meatball-soup-5c477ed0c445fa5d6d508ef2
course: main course
---

Adjust oven rack to top position and preheat broiler to high. Wash and dry all
produce. Trim and peel @carrot{1}(peeled and halved), then cut into ½-inch pieces.
Halve @yellow onion{1/2}(peeled and diced). Mince @garlic{2%cloves}. Remove and
discard any large ribs from @kale{4%oz}; chop leaves into 1-inch pieces.

Heat a large drizzle of @olive oil{2%teaspoon} in a #large pot{} over medium heat.
Add carrot, onion, and half the garlic. Cook, stirring occasionally, until softened,
~{8-10%minutes}.

> TIP: If veggies cook too quickly, lower heat to medium low.

While veggies cook, in a #medium bowl{}, combine @ground pork{10%oz},
@panko breadcrumbs{1/4%cup}, half the @Tuscan Heat Spice{1%tablespoon},
and a few big pinches of @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}. Shape mixture into small
½-inch-wide meatballs.

Stir remaining Tuscan Heat Spice into #pot{} with veggies. Cook until fragrant,
about ~{30%seconds}. Stir in kale, @chicken stock concentrate{2}, 3 cups hot water,
and a few big pinches of salt. Cover pot, increase heat to high, and bring soup to a
boil. Once boiling, remove lid. Carefully stir in @orzo pasta{1/3%cup} and meatballs.
Reduce heat to medium low and cover. Cook until orzo is al dente and meatballs are
cooked, about ~{10%minutes}.

Meanwhile, halve @demi-baguette{1} lengthwise, then halve again on an angle. Place
@butter{2%tablespoon} in a #small microwave-safe bowl{}; microwave until softened,
about ~{15%seconds}. Stir in remaining garlic and season with salt. Spread onto cut
sides of demi-baguette. Place on a #baking sheet{} cut sides up. Place under broiler
and toast until golden, ~{2-3%minutes}.

> TIP: Keep an eye out the entire time for any burning.

Stir half the @Parmesan cheese{1/4%cup} into soup. Season with salt and pepper.
Divide soup between #bowls{}; sprinkle with remaining Parmesan. Serve with garlic
bread on the side.